{
  "texts": [
    "The following sections describe the experimental setup, datasets and promps along with the error analysis conducted.",
    "For the experiments, we accessed 23 ChatGPT (based on GPT-3.5) through the API.",
    "Given that the related work on using GPT models for MT highlighted the importance of (explicit) prompting, we looked at two different prompting scenarios.",
    "We used a subset of an existing challenge dataset, gENder-IT (Vanmassenhove and Monti, 2021), designed specifically for resolving natural gender phenomena in translation contexts.",
    "The challenge set is a word-level (human) annotated, adapted and cleaned version of a subset of the MuST-SHE corpus (Bentivogli et al., 2020), but unlike MuST-SHE which is annotated on the paragraph level, the sentences have been split and annotated on the word-level with <F> (female), <M> (male) or <A> (ambiguous) tags."
  ]
}